node.text: The crew on the road with @independenttrucks

Ever find yourself hunched in a ball under a handrail at the bottom of some stairs kneeling in a sticky oily substance that is most likely 25 generations of bum urine that has puddled up and dried until it forms a viscous jelly - and your back has been bent for 2 consecutive hours and will need to be medically straightened using the help of high-end chiropractic professionals outside of your insurance network? THEN WE HAVE SOMETHING JUST FOR YOU! The #DonLuong ( @yerdone )FILMER CRUISER, specifically designed for the discriminating auteur by Mr. Luong himself to be the perfect balance of width and shape to enhance your filmmaking by 35%. A versatile construction allows it to be used as a shred-stick for those filmers that also rip hard but somehow ended up filming their friends who are not even as talented as they are, and then on demand it can be used as a barrier to stop a deck from shooting into traffic, or outfitted with softer wheels for shooting a stealthy line in total silence.

This deck is 8.5 inches wide and has a graphic designed by Ed Templeton and Don Luong in celebration of filmers worldwide and the under-celebrated work they do!

Don Luong has been an integral part of Toy Machine (and Foundation too) over the last 10 years! His talent, vision and extraordinary skill are instrumental to what make the bloodsucking corporation what it is. Thank you Don! - Ed

Video by - @codylonglens @frankjake
